SB 282 Original 2026 Regular Session Barrow
Proposed law provides for the creation of an economic development district that includes
property owned by Baton Rouge Community College ("the district"). The purpose of such
a district is to provide for cooperative economic and community development among the
district, the colleges, the parish or municipal governing authority, the state, and the owners
of property in the district.
Proposed law provides that such a district is governed by a board of commissioners,
comprised as follows:
(1) The highest executive officer of the college.
